 <h4>Answer the following questions to write a paragraph on ‘Premature Marriage’. You should write it in about 250 words ᐅ</h4>
 <br><br>
 <h3><center>Premature Marriage</center></h3>
 
<p>Early marriage means the marriage between a boy and a girl below the age of 18. According to who, the marriage age limit is 21 for males and 18 for females. Any marriage before their figure of age is considered early marriage. Generally, rural boys and girls from illiterate and poverty-stricken families are the primary victims of it. There are various causes of early marriage. Among them, poverty, ignorance, superstitions, and lack of awareness are remarkable. Early marriage does not bring any good to society. Immature males and females cannot adjust themselves to their marital life. Again, being a mother at an early age, a female cannot play the role of a birth mother. Moreover, she is attacked by various diseases due to malnutrition. She faces the risk of her life. Her body does not find great milk available. Thus, the subsequent generation of society becomes affected. Early marriage is also responsible for the population explosion. To solve this problem, early marriage must be stopped. Mass education should be ensured. Social awareness must be developed. For this, the government and the ordinary people must work together.</p>
